<L>__{interior car a bit later}
<A>__{the sun has come up strong. it looks hot. laroche speeds along with one finger on the wheel, paying little attention to the road. the car veers onto the shoulder, he lazily corrects it. orlean is tense.}
<C>__{laroche}
<D>__{i remember one time when i was a kid, fifteen or so, my mother and i came to the fakahatchee to look for a ghost to photograph. we walked for hours, through the most intense heat i'd ever felt. we couldn't find one. i wanted to turn back. but my mom said, no.}
<C>__{laroche }
<D>__{she said, john, if you keep searching for something past doubt, past hopelessness, past the absolute certainty that you'll never find it, if you keep searching past that, there it'll be. so we walked. i had goddamn bloody blisters on my feet. and we found ourselves in this charred prairie, desolate, sun blasted, y'know. and there in the middle of it was this one gorgeous, snowy polyrrhiza lindenii.}
<A>__{they drive in silence for a little while. she watches him.}
